{
  "abstract": "Thirteen cultivars differing in reaction to grain moulds (caused by a range of unspecialized fungi, including Curvularia lunata [Cochliobolus lunatus] and Fusarium multilforme [Gibberella fujikuroi]) showed differences in contents of polyphenols, including flavan-4-ols and proanthocyanidins. In particular, levels of flavan-4-ols in grain and leaf extracts (but not callus) of resistant cultivars were 2-3 times higher than those found in susceptible cultivars",
